NBC's Nancy Snyderman has been told to 'take some time off' after she broke her Ebola quarantine to visit her favorite soup restaurant.

The 62-year-old medical correspondent was ordered to avoid all human contact for 21 days as doctors treated her cameraman Ashoka Mukpo after he contracted the deadly virus in Liberia.

Despite this, Dr Snyderman and her team visited the Peasant Grill soup restaurant in New Jersey, sparking fears that Ebola could spread further.

